 My buddies in High School were keenly aware of the older gutys in our small town going and mostly returning from Vietnam. We knew how it affected them and respected them before it was cool to thank a vet for doing his duty. The fact that we didn't have to go was okay to them.<br>
 Today I still tell vets I meet simply &quot;thanks&quot;. Sometimes a word can say alot.
